      "writtenOn": "2018-06-20T19:40:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sorry, didn\u0027t think about this on the previous review.\n\nSuppose there are two concurrent requests (they get the same timeStampMs) that both triage the same digest differently. One will win, and we don\u0027t care too much which one.\n\nHowever, it\u0027s possible that the \"winner\" (the request that was processed second) will end up with a TimeSortableKey that sorts before the \"loser,\" due to the random component. Then, when we call CalcExpectations, the \"loser\" will become the \"winner\" because it will appear that the loser\u0027s change came second.\n\nWe probably still don\u0027t care too much, but it\u0027s a little unfortunate that we can \"change history\" like this.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 288,
        "startChar": 33,
        "endLine": 288,
        "endChar": 47
      },
      "revId": "8c29b397e72ee54b8ccf6de535c9067d63e17201",
